//www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Everybody's Favorite Hero</span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/01 2:40:49 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://people.we.mediaone.net/nateman/Jaikar/jaikarphoto.jpg border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Hit, not Sit</span><hr size=1> Ye only taunts when the foe be lookin' the other way! Otherwise, it won't be refreshed and ready ta go when ye REALLY needs it (cleric gettin' whacked on). Tauntin' anythin' that's already aggro'd on ye won't do nuthin' other than ta waste yer chance o' pullin' a creature offa yer huntin' partner later on.<br>
<br>
There ain't no preventive mainenance when it comes ta Tauntin'. Ye can't makes the foe hate ye any more if ye already gots it's attention -- yer either at the top o' the hate list or ye ain't. So's best thing ta do is hold off onna Tauntin' 'til the creature turns its head.<br>
<br>
If ye wants ta throw in Disarm and Beg and whutever else, fine...but sittin' down?! I dunno 'bouts that one. Ta stop attackin', sit down, stand up, then start attackin' again...no matter how fast ye does it, ye gots ta be losin' out on at least a coupla swings there. Now factor in how many times ye plan on Tauntin' in such a manner. Add it all up, and ye probably missed out on whut? 10? 20? 30? 40 swings o' yer blade? Now add in the crits, crips, procs, and damage that ye also missed out on...Then figure out how much less effective ye became as a tank each time yer foe whacked ye HARD while sittin' down (since we all know they seems ta hit harder when yer sittin' on yer arse)...Not ta mention how foolish ye'll look sittin' up and down...<br>
<br>
...I fer one wouldn't do the sittin' thing. <p><CENTER> <IMG SRC="http://people.we.mediaone.net/nateman/Jaikar/jaikarsig.jpg" BORDER=0> </CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukazarksnaketongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazark Snaketongue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/01 6:06:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hit, not Sit</span><hr size=1> Best thing to do is get right up on that mob and keep swinging.  The more hits you land the more the mob will get pissed.<br>
